thread.title: Muted Start for Asia Stocks

author: wsjcom
title: Muted Start for Asia Stocks
text:
Fed decision, U.S.-China trade in focus Major indexes slightly higher Treasury yields and dollar inch lower U.S. stocks inched higher Wednesday after the Federal Reserve left interest rates unchanged and signaled no plans to pick up the pace of rate increases in response to firming inflation.
The Dow Jones Industrial Average reversed earlier losses and was recently up 52 points, or 0.2%, to 24151. The S&P 500 added 0.1%, and the Nasdaq Composite was up 0.3%.
